    flow:uploadTimestamp "2025-11-08T17:25:14.676807+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    dcterms:description "The resource is a step‑by‑step video tutorial that introduces users to Anytype, an offline‑first application for organizing notes, data tables, and other personal information. It begins by explaining how to download the software from anytype.io and create a new “space,” the primary container for content, showing how to add a fresh space or start from an existing one. The presenter demonstrates basic navigation, including hiding the sidebar for a cleaner view, and walks through creating a new page using the plus‑button menu. Key customization options are highlighted: adding an emoji or image icon, selecting a cover image from Unsplash or personal uploads, editing the page description, and adjusting layout width and header position. The tutorial also covers the concept of object types, templates, and default settings, illustrating how to edit type properties such as default layout, title visibility, and checkbox inclusion for tasks. It notes that notes omit a title so the entire body becomes searchable, and briefly mentions tagging as a property. Overall, the guide aims to familiarize new users with Anytype’s core features and customization capabilities." ;
    dcterms:title "A_Complete_Guide_to_Anytype!(720p).mp4" .

